you can use two ways start with docker if you have or start with your python
Way 1 Python:
before download activate your virtual env for python or you can continue it in your machine python
we need Python 3.9

before start, download all packages from requirements.txt
```
    pip install -r requirements.txt
```

to start run on terminal
```
    uvicorn main:app --reload
```
Way 2 Docker
1st command
    docker build -t my-app .
2nd command
    docker run -p 8000:8000 my-app
